  "body": "Hi! I just want to ask if I did the right thing on my node. Here's the things that I did.\r\n\r\n1. I created a folder named \"NODE\" and installed geth app on my external HDD (D:)\r\n2. I ran the node with geth --http --datadir D:\\NODE command\r\n\r\nI specifically wants to connect on Localhost:8545 on Metamask using Chain ID 1 and etherscan.io block explorer but it's not working.\r\nWhen I tried to manually edit the information of Localhost network and change the Chain ID from 1337 to 1 so that I will be on mainnet network while using Localhost and etherscan.io for the Block Explorer, my ETH balance are not showing up. It seems like I am not connected to the mainnet.\r\n\r\nIs there something wrong with the things that I've mentioned about how I ran my node? Please, help. Thank you.",
